verses.text:
Like a swallow  a crane, so did I chatter;
I did moan as a dove; mine eyes fail  upward:
O Lord, I am oppressed, be thou my surety.

O Lord, by these things men live;
And wholly therein is the life of my spirit:
 <i>[k]</i>Wherefore recover thou me, and make me to live.

Behold, for peace I had great bitterness:
But <i>[l]</i>thou hast in love to my soul delivered it from the pit of <i>[m]</i>corruption;
   For thou hast cast all my sins behind thy back.
